## Developer setup

### Requirements
- Android Studio (Hedgehog or newer) **or** any IDE with Kotlin + Gradle support
- JDK 17+
- Git

### Steps

```bash
# 1. Fork https://github.com/recloudstream/TestPlugins  (required template)
# 2. Clone YOUR fork
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_GITHUB_USERNAME/AnimeKaiProvider.git
cd AnimeKaiProvider

# 3. Copy the files from this repo into your fork

# 4. Build a test APK and sideload to your device
./gradlew AnimeKaiProvider:deployWithAdb   # deploys directly if adb is connected

# -- OR -- build .cs3 file manually
./gradlew AnimeKaiProvider:make
# Output: builds/AnimeKaiProvider.cs3
```

### Enabling auto-builds (GitHub Actions)

1. Push to GitHub.
2. Go to **Settings → Actions → General** → select **Allow all actions and reusable workflows**.
3. Go to **Settings → Actions → General → Workflow permissions** → select **Read and write permissions**.
4. Every push to `main` will now auto-build and deploy to the `builds` branch.

